Five stars for the front-desk's cheerful and "make-right" attitude.	Why exactly is this hotel considered a four star luxury hotel anyways?	There is a very nice upscale market roughly one block west of the hotel called "Urban Fare".	I realize this is what five-star service is about, but I still worried about finding my luggage on the sidewalk when I returned to the hotel.	Hotel was very clean and upscale.	High End Hotel with excellent service, great food and incredible view of the bay.	Other so-called 4 star hotels should learn from this attitude.	If you are feeling "touristy" go ahead and see Granville island.